==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|southerne|lang=enm}}, {{term|sothern|lang=enm}}, {{term|sutherne|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|suþerne|sūþerne|southern, southerly, coming from the south; of southern make|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|sunþra||southwards|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|sun-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|swen-||sun|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|southron|lang=sco}}, {{term|sudron||southern|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|suthern|sūthern|lang=ofs}}, {{term|sudern|sūdern|southern|lang=ofs}}, {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|sudern|sūdern|southern|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|sundern||southern|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|súðrænn||southern, tropical|lang=is}}. More at {{l|en|south}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈsʌðə(r)n/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"sVD@(r)n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-southern.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of, facing, situated in, or related to the [[south]].
# Of or pertaining to a southern region, especially Southern Europe or the southern United States.
#: ''The southern climate.''
# Of a [[wind]]: [[blow]]ing from the south; [[southerly]].

